});
```

---

### 6. 🕵️ `X-Powered-By` Header Exposure
Express advertises itself via the `X-Powered-By: Express` header by default, giving attackers free information.

**Disable it:**
```js
app.disable('x-powered-by');
```
*(Note: `helmet` handles this automatically — see #2)*

---

### 7. 🪵 No Structured Logging
`console.log` in production is unstructured and difficult to trace. Consider a library like [`pino`](https://getpino.io/) or [`winston`](https://github.com/winstonjs/winston) for structured, level-based logging.

